library(corrplot)
library(viridis)
## Loading required package: viridisLite
colors <- viridis(n = 3, begin = 0.2, end = 0.8, option = "mako")

m1 <- matrix(c(1, .3, .3, .3, .3, .3,
               .3, 1, .3, .3, .3, .3,
               .3, .3, 1, .3, .3, .3,
               .3, .3, .3, 1, .3, .3,
               .3, .3, .3, .3, 1, .3,
               .3, .3, .3, .3, .3, 1),nrow=6)
rownames(m1) <- colnames(m2) <- c("x1","x2","x3","x4","x5","x6")
corrplot(m1,
         method = "square", 
         addCoef.col = 1,
         diag = TRUE,
         outline = FALSE,
         type = "lower",
         col = colorRampPalette(c(colors[1], colors[2], colors[3]))(100),
         tl.cex = 1,
         cl.cex = 1,
         tl.col = "black",
         tl.srt = 0,
         tl.offset = .8,
         number.font = 1)

m1_mean_r <- mean(m1[lower.tri(m1)])
m1_mean_r
## [1] 0.3
m1_alpha <- psych::alpha(m1)$total$raw_alpha
m1_alpha
## [1] 0.72
